b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48217.htm)  [Next](sbe48219.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n13\\. And because (the world also) would thus be eternal.\n\np. 499\n\nThe samavaya is a relation, and if that relation is eternal that to which the\nrelation belongs must also be eternal, so that we would arrive at the\nunacceptable conclusion that the world is eternal.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 14. And on account of the atoms having colour](sbe48219.htm)\n\n'